transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, this is Jimmy, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Jimmy, this is Ed Selner.

Speaker 1: Can I give you my phone number so that you can dial into my account?

Speaker 2: You sure can.

Speaker 1: I believe I have it up, unless you have a different one.

Speaker 2: I have the 651-263-7089.

Speaker 1: Is that a good number for you?

Speaker 2: That's it.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Not a problem.

Speaker 1: Let me just go ahead and pull that up for you and see what I come up with.

Speaker 2: Give me one second.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, Mr. Selner, I do have you up.

Speaker 1: And how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Well, I had been getting the score blue.

Speaker 1: It wasn't working for me.

Speaker 2: And it was at least two months ago I called in to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And then the guy – and I didn't ask for a refund.

Speaker 1: I think there was a refund that was supposed to come.

Speaker 2: But anyway, so then the guy said, well, I'll send you an extra strong one.

Speaker 1: It will be free.

Speaker 2: And so I said, okay.

Speaker 1: So he sent it.

Speaker 2: It doesn't work.

Speaker 1: I'm too old.

Speaker 2: I've resigned to that fact.

Speaker 1: But for the last two weeks I received billings on two more subscriptions.

Speaker 2: On January 2nd, I was billed $63.95.

Speaker 1: And on January 16th, which is about 10 days ago, I was billed another $63.95.

Speaker 2: And I haven't received them.

Speaker 1: Go ahead.

Speaker 2: I'm looking at what I'm seeing on the phone number that you gave me.

Speaker 1: You sounded good up to the January the 1st, 2nd call,

Speaker 2: because I do see that you was refunded that $63.95 for the one that was for

Speaker 1: January the 1st.

Speaker 2: I do see they did send you the new and improved Viagra in December.

Speaker 1: And they did that for free.

Speaker 2: They didn't charge you on that one.

Speaker 1: And the one charge that was done in January, it was reversed.

Speaker 2: So they refunded you for that.

Speaker 1: And they currently on 1-12, they canceled your prescription.

Speaker 2: So, therefore, you wouldn't be receiving anything else.

Speaker 1: So I'm not exactly sure what the one you're talking about, the 1-16, would be,

Speaker 2: because I'm not showing anything as far as that on your record,

Speaker 1: other than what I just mentioned to you now.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: Well, I just checked my bank account,

Speaker 2: and that's what it shows is the January 2nd I was charged and January 16th I

Speaker 1: was charged.

Speaker 2: Oh, you know what?

Speaker 1: Check the one for January 16th to make sure that's not a credit.

Speaker 2: That should be a credit.

Speaker 1: That's not a debit.

Speaker 2: So double check that.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: Because that's approximately when the refund should have hit,

Speaker 1: because they did a refund on the 12th.

Speaker 2: And that's probably a refund and not a debit.

Speaker 1: I mean, not a charge.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Well, that was really good, if that's true.

Speaker 2: I will check it.

Speaker 1: But would you make sure that my subscription is canceled?

Speaker 2: You are canceled.

Speaker 1: That's the last thing I mentioned to you.

Speaker 2: That was done on the 12th.

Speaker 1: That was done on the 12th when the refund was issued.

Speaker 2: So the thing you looked at on the 16th, no doubt,

Speaker 1: it's probably a refund credit, not another charge.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I will certainly check on that.

Speaker 2: Thank you for your help.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: Have a great day.

Speaker 2: You too, Jimmy.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
